The National Commissioner of the South African Police
Service, General Khehla John Sitole returned to work on Tuesday after receiving
a clean bill of health on Monday. Police spokesperson, Brigadier Vish Naidoo, said General
Sitole tested positive for Covid-19 approximately 14 days ago
but he has been completely asymptomatic during his recovery. He said the National Commissioner is glad that he was able to
recover from this devastating virus which has taken more than 27 000 lives.